Enugu State Government has declared Wednesday, February 23 work-free day to enable residents vote for their choice candidates in the state’s local governments election. This is contained in a statement on Sunday in Enugu by the Special Adviser to the governor on Information, Mr Steve Oruruo. Oruruo said: “The Enugu State Government wishes to notify the public that Local Government Area election in the state will hold on Wednesday, Feb. 23, 2022. “Consequently, the government has declared work-free day from 8am to 4pm to allow the people exercise their suffrage.’’